Text: Jullus has told us all. You have Lord Gnaeus's permission to enter and speak with our residents, but not to petition them directly for support. Remember that.
Still no word from Martyn, but never fear─it shouldn't be long before he's found a prospective rival for you.
To be honest, it's hard to picture Martyn as a villain, even if he's only acting.
By the sounds of it, Royse has afforded Martyn more than an unfair advantage, so don't worry about holding back.

Well, well, well... If it isn't my old nemesis... <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>.
Ahem. Stilll tryin' to wrap my head around this villainous banter, but don't you worry─I'll get it eventually.
Good show, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Good show...
I haven't a mean bone in my body, yet somehow Royse expects me to take on a dark persona to play your nemesis. Hopefully she knows what she's doing.
While our present welfare is important, we must be willing to endure hardship if it helps us to secure our nation's future. Strong leaders like Lord Gnaeus understand this.
Keep your voice down. There are people resting inside.
Ser Estinien has told me Varshahn remains as determined as ever to rescue his sister.
For our part, the Radiant Host will spare no effort to defend Radz-at-Han, and I pray that you will continue assisting our “little brother” in his efforts.
In the wake of the explosion in Alzadaal's Legacy, it was decided that we need to retain eyes over our waters. This outpost will remain in place for a while yet.
I swear, our morale palpably improves whenever you pay us a visit. Don't be a stranger, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>!
It is most regrettable that I cannot accompany you, but so be it. I pray you can help restore the natural balance of Aloalo.
Pasasun seems to enjoy doting upon me. When my wings have healed and I am free to return home, I wonder if he would follow?
Truth be told, it is not an entirely distasteful prospect. He has done much for me, after all. Allowing him to pamper me even more seems a just reward for his efforts!
Those unaccustomed to the odor of our alchemical agents can find them overpowering, so I must take care not to use anything too pungent when treating Kalika.
His strength is returning slowly but steadily, and it may soon be time to prepare proper meals for him. I wonder what dish he would like best...?
This unit has café operations fully under control. Whether the would-be-visionary life-form will come up with a decent idea is more difficult to calculate with certainty.
Did you know that those little Loporrits are on the radio now? My friend invited me to listen to the race they broadcasted the other day.
I'm not much of an aetherologist─and certainly no xenobiologist─so I can only wonder what sort of magicks were at work there...
These radio news reports are even more outlandish than what they publish in the gazette! That “Hyper Hustle” story gave me a good laugh, though.
You recall the gleaner friend I mentioned to you? He introduced me to Hope FM─and I'm so glad he did! My heart is still pounding from the excitement of the Hyper Hustle...
I'll be here when you're ready to race again. Ever since the Hyper Hustle, I've been makin' time to practice.
Workin' hard's a necessity, but for a while there I'd forgotten what it's all for. Sometimes you need the rush of the winds flappin' your ears to get a little perspective, you know?
The grub that Boss brought back was one swift kick to the nose!
I ain't got a clue what kinda spice was in it, but it'd knock a lotta Arkasodara right out. Good thing I can handle spicy food better'n most.
For learning, I took my hippo on a walk. Always, it smelled the flowers.
Now I know the secret. The secret of potpourri!
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! We've been getting loads of reports of people on Etheirys discussing our broadcast of the Hyper Hustle.
Talkingway is over the moon! Literally, of course, as we all are, but also in a manner of speaking!
Our listeners seem to have enjoyed the Hyper Hustle far more than I dreamed. According to some recent letters, they've even begun meeting at the Last Stand to discuss our broadcasts.
This means, of course, that we must redouble our efforts to bring them compelling content─all day and all night!
More batteries! MORE!!!
...That is to say, I'm hard at work on an extra-improved moon-hopper for the next hustle. Those hippos won't know what hit 'em!
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! I'm happy to report that since the Hyper Hustle, there have been no further mass exoduses of our clientele. In fact, business has never been better.
We'll always have a table for you, though, so stop by any time!
I had some reservations about restoring a Peacekeeper, but you know how he is when he gets an idea into his head. Though I admit, I wouldn't say no to another turn around the track!
We continue to find conversations about racing practices...invigorating. Is our yearning for victory the cause─or the discussion in itself?
Perhaps all we truly require is this place.
I don't like the sound o' this. Not one soddin' bit.
That Manderville weaponry o' yers treatin' ye well, then? 'Course it bloody is.
If yer thinkin' o' makin' another, then Master Smallclothes over there is jus' as soddin' eager as ever. Jus' say the word.
As I may have mentioned, there are other weapon variants we have yet to reforge. I am prepared to stay the course until the final armament is perfected!
Enjoying a hard-earned rest, I trust? ...Don't tell me Mother has called on you for business.
I'll not deny it is good to be home, but it would be a lie to say Garlemald and her people do not yet weigh on my mind. Surely, there is something more we can do ensure their warmth and comfort.
How was the banquet? A pity I couldn't go with you─it would have been good to see everyone.

Even so, I've enjoyed my time here with Mother and Father. Speaking of which, he's expressed an interest in sitting down with you, so don't be surprised to receive a formal invitation from him in future.
We insisted that Alphinaud and Alisaie take their rest, but you're no less deserving of respite.
To see you fight so tirelessly for causes greater than yourself, be they here or even in altogether different worlds, there's little wonder why you're revered as a hero.
Time and again we have witnessed you make the seemingly impossible possible, and it is nothing short of inspiring. Needless to say, we'll be striving to follow your example.

When my sister has strength enough to fly beyond the clouds, I would share with her the beauty of Thavnair. We will soar the skies by starlight as we did in our youth, and gaze upon its natural splendor.
Radz-at-Han... Home...

Alphinaud and Alisaie have returned home, have they? With rebuilding efforts proceeding as they are, it was only a matter of time. I imagine it will not be long before the Ilsabard contingent prepares to withdraw as well.
We were most glad to hear your operation on the moon proved a success. It is a relief to know we may safely make use of the tower once more.
Blessed be! Azdaja has been returned to us! There must be a feast─a grand banquet to celebrate her homecoming!
Varshahn. My dear little brother... He will be all right, won't he?
It pained me deeply to think we might have lost the satrap, and it was only then that I began to know the heartache he bore from his sister's absence.
By that same token, I better understand his joy at their reunion. Indeed, my heart was full to bursting at their safe return.
Master Vrtra and his sister are returned!
There will be a feast to celebrate, and I daresay the whole of Radz-at-Han will be present. I should hope you can find time to attend as well.
Though the mission is complete, there is still so much I wish to learn of the void.

Naturally, I thought to seek out Azdaja. Then I remembered how, when speaking with Y'shtola of the First, my enthusiasm carried us well into the early hours of the morning. I hope not to make that same mistake again.
I heard the news from Master Fourchenault. Glad to know you put that aether from the Isle of Haam to good use.
Now I can finally focus on me work─a new aetherburner. One that'll see you to the moon with a single, bombastic blast!
Worry not─I will see to preparation of the tower. The rest I leave to you.
Thanks to the Exarch's instructions, the tower is ready to deliver Light to the void. But pray do not let me keep you─there is yet work to be done.
All is in readiness, I see. Excellent. Soon we shall be ready to deliver Light to the void.
It will not take me long to place Zero's soul in the spirit vessel. I will meet you in the Ocular when I have finished.
The rest is up to you and the others in the Source. All will be well. Of this I have no doubt.
<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>!? What are you doing here? Whatever business brought you, it will have to wait. I must insist you return to the others.
'Tis good to see you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. If you're come to discuss what became of your mission, perhaps we should speak in the Ocular that Ryne and Lyna may join us.
If you were intending to offer compensation for my assistance, that will not be necessary. To have played a part in delivering the light of hope to the void was fitting payment in itself.
I have spoken with the people of the Crystarium, and they were more than understanding of your plight. When arrangements have been made to place your transmitters, I will contact you via whisperweed.
Thank you again for speaking with the people of Eulmore and Rak'tika. All that remains is to set your plan into motion.
My apologies, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, but I was given to believe your mission is not yet complete. In which case, I must ask that you return to your comrades.
So the mission was a success. That is well. Let us go to the Ocular and share the glad tidings with Ryne and Beq Lugg.
To see the whole of Norvrandt come together for a singular purpose was heartening to say the least. I've no doubt that selfsame camaraderie will serve us well as we continue to rebuild.
After everything you've done for us, helping you to Nabaath Areng was the least I could do. If there's ever anything else you need, don't hesitate to ask.
In all my years, never did I imagine I would help anyone to wield the power of Light. There's never a dull moment when you're involved, is there?
My thanks again for your consideration of our citizens. The rest, you may leave to us.
It is a relief to know that all has gone to plan. Thanks to you, the people of Eulmore were quite receptive to my explanation of the situation.
Indeed, they were able to set aside their apprehensions and came together, supporting one another in service to a greater goal. Truly, a testament to the unified city Eulmore has become.
I cannot promise we will always have the strength needed to aid you, but you shall ever be welcome here in Eulmore.
Brief though it was, it was wonderful to see you. Do visit again when the situation has settled in your world.
My, what a welcome surprise! If you're here, then I take it your home is safe once more? We were so terribly worried...
Should you ever find yourself in need of aid, please never hesitate to call on us. Of course, you need not only visit in times of crisis.
Though we are worlds apart, we will continue to pray for your happiness. You, Alphinaud, Zero, and all of your friends there in the Source.
Eulmore owes the Crystarium a debt for its consideration of our people. We look forward to our continued cooperation.
We received word that Light could be seen amassing at the Crystal Tower from as far as Kholusia.

Naturally, there was concern the sight might incite fear in the public, but much to our relief, the people were comforted by the knowledge that this gathering of Light was to aid the Warrior of Darkness.
As you may have guessed, Master Chai was rather restless as well, pacing about the plaza all the while. No one was more relieved than he to see the people's reaction.
Zero seemed pessimistic for her world, but we will pray for it all the same. Take care, my friend, and give my regards to Master Matoya.
All has gone as Master Matoya planned, then. I would expect nothing less.
I should hope to congratulate her in person someday.
You may leave matters here to us. Just promise me you'll not cause any trouble for Ryne, all right?

It is good to see you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Ryne as well. By all accounts, she has grown to be a remarkable young woman, and it puts my mind at ease to know she remains in high spirits.
It is never an easy thing to be separated from those we care for, but even when they are gone, their memories will remain to give us comfort.
Is something wrong? If you have need of the trolley, you're always more than welcome.
I was wondering: are there trolleys in your world as well? And engineers to give them their due adoration?
I intend to find such like-minded souls here, and I'll lay down tracks across every ilm of Norvrandt to do it!
I can't remember the last time I've seen Jeryk so excited... And I'm not sure if I should be concerned.
Twine remains the same as it's always been, and while we don't have much, I'm glad we could still be of help to you.
Even when we build this town back into a bustling center of business, you can always count on us.
The merchants of Mord Souq will ever be at the ready to help customers in need. You may leave your transmitters to us!
When discussing the placement of your transmitters, we found ourselves on the subject of the Nabaath Severance and its derelict gondola.

Should Light's hold on the Empty weaken, Mord Souq can branch out, expand to new locations. Such a vessel would then prove valuable. I trust you will come to our new market, yes? Come with coin and partake of our wares.
Well come, ally of Ronka. We were recently visited by Runar of Slitherbough, and he has shared with us much of your recent trials.
As the guardians of these woods, full well do we understand your duty to protect your home. To preserve the wisdom of those who came before, that it may serve those to come after.
May your home always know peace and plenty, and its people the courage to keep it.
It has been a long time. Too long, perhaps. I fear you're starting to look like a wrinkled old grape.
Hah, I jest, I jest! The Night's Blessed have told us of your endeavors. Peace has been restored, but do you not worry that boredom may soon follow?
Cymet often complains of the wood's tedium, and her desire to travel beyond our borders. Mayhap one day you could take her on one of your adventures!
Oh, what a welcome surprise! I did not think you would honor us again with your presence so soon!

It was my hope that our next meeting might be beyond the borders of the Greatwood. Indeed, I wish to live among the peoples of Lakeland for a time, but Almet insists my presence would prove nothing more than a nuisance.
Even so, I will not be deterred. My journey will be a long one─ten years, in fact─so I must take my time to be duly prepared, and say farewell to my sisters.
Come to speak with Ryne, have you? Well, don't keep her for too long. I was planning a trip to Il Mheg, but knowing how devious the fae folk can be, I asked her to join me.
I also wouldn't mind visiting Amaurot someday. It's been on my mind of late, and it would be interesting to see where those two lived in the time of the ancients, if only once.
I've no doubt there is much you wish to know about Tural, but there will be plenty of time to answer your questions on the journey there.
I will see to our supplies. All you need do is be patient─it will be time to depart before you know it.
A shame we have to leave to Tural so soon. I would've loved to visit Eorzea, or at the very least see more of Sharlayan.
What I have seen is pretty impressive, though. I wasn't expecting a city of scholars to carry such impressive arms in their shops.
Never did I imagine that I might travel to Tural, much less be involved in a contest to decide its new ruler. I shall do all in my power to see that Wuk Lamat succeeds.
And in so doing, I expect I will learn a great deal that will be of help to Jullus and his people. I can think of no better way to make the most of my time away from Garlemald.
Is it strange that, after traveling to the literal edge of existence, a simple journey across the ocean has me so excited?
In any case, after hearing of Krile's exploits on the Isle of Haam, it seems I have my work cut out for me if I'm to keep up.
The only clues I have to Grandfather's business in Tural are his letter and the earring he enclosed with it.
I thought perhaps if I wear it, and someone there recognizes it, they may offer further insights as to why he was there.

I meant it when I said we were boldly goin' where no tradesperson's gone afore...an' I ain't quittin' before the end. With proper preparations and a bit o' determination, we'll be pioneerin' a brand new age o' trade in no time.

Me life has only changed for the better since ye wandered into it, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. If it weren't for yer efforts, Miss Chora-Zoi an' I may not have dared to dream up the splendorous tools...an' I reckon I'd still be a blubberin', lovesick fool.
Aye, yer determination inspired us to forge ahead─an' we'll do our damndest to make ye proud. If there's aught ye need from us in the days ahead, just say the word.

Just watching Master Grenoldt's proposal was making me anxious... I'm relieved it went well, but we're not out of the woods yet! We must ensure these final splendorous tools will exceed Mistress Mowen's every expectation and more!

A pleasure as always to see you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! You'll be pleased to know that our splendorous tools continue to garner critical acclaim across the realm...which means we've been inundated with orders from the Boutique.
Our hands may be full, but the toil is more than worth it! And don't worry─if you require any further tool enhancements, we'll be sure to make time for them. It's the least we can do!

Our tools flourish throughout Norvrandt, and Mistress Mowen has reunited with her beloved... As a representative of the Boutique, words cannot well express my gratitude for your cooperation. We owe you a great debt, and shall continue to serve you as best we can.
I find myself gazing at Grenoldt's kettle more often than not. Though we are parted, our hearts are as one─and I could not be happier for it.

You have my thanks, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Norvrandt's trades shall surely prosper, and I eagerly await the bright future ahead...as well as your continued patronage, of course.
Chora-Zoi and Grenoldt were determined to finish that splendorous tool of theirs, and I'm pleased to know their hard work's paid off. You should all be proud of what you've created─I certainly am.
We've not received our finished tools yet, but the leaders of the Facets won't stop chatting about them. Their curiosity's been piqued ever since Chora-Zoi came to us with her list of questions.
Needless to say, we're eager to put your work to the test! In the meantime, you'd do well to speak with the others. May as well regale them on the splendors to come, eh?

You know, it's not easy guiding the Enterprise through a ceaselessly swirling wall of wind. I would rather not risk our lives again until you're sure─meaning absolutely certain─that you're ready. Are you?
The crowd is as lively as I've ever seen it! Would that Peatie could be our star every year!
I know you and Peatie'll have adventures wilder than any I could ever imagine. Make sure to come visit and regale me with your tales, eh?
Ah, you came after all! As you can see, the citizens cannot get enough of Hatching–tide. Go on and enjoy yourself!
An eggcellent and eggciting Hatching–tide to you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! We hope you enjoy all that we've prepared this year!
The sylphs had a bit too much fun last year, so we've put tonberry eggs here and there to keep those tricksters away.
Looking at them now, though... I only hope they don't scare away more revelers than sylphs.
I must say, the organizers of the festivities have outdone themselves! That goobbue turned me into an egg fanatic!
Riggy do trick! See Riggy's trick!
I came here during my break to see how the festivities were coming along, but imagine my surprise when I heard tell of a performing goobbue! I had to see it for myself.

Ah, it seems you've caught me in a rather precarious predicament. I've been pursuing new means of acquiring gil, you see. Thinking of potential endeavors we might undertake in future, it wouldn't do to find my coffers wanting at a critical juncture.

Hmmm... Perhaps I should consider the Loporrits' treasure vault that Urianger spoke of. In any case, so long as they do not interfere with my obligations to the Students of Baldesion, I intend to pursue all possible avenues.
\\<heavy breathing> Eggs! Tonberry eggs! Heeeeee! Such adorable decorations are sure to turn tonberries from symbols of terror to objects of adoration!

When I heard that the Gold Saucer took a new approach to their annual celebration, I thought it best to report my findings and write something up before my rivals had the chance, but now that I've seen it for myself, I'm not quite sure where to begin...

<split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! Glad am I to find a familiar face among these halls. I am come on behalf of Lord Hien to investigate the creatures you know as water imps. In the Far East, we call them kappa, and they oft appear in our myths.

My lord was unusually intrigued by reports of the imps' appearance, and would not rest until he learned more of this phenomenon. Yet his position allows him little time for such trivial matters, and thus did I travel here in his stead.

Know you of the muscular imp that roams the Saucer? 'Twas no sooner after I arrived that he bestowed upon me this suit of attire. Perhaps I shall wear it again upon my return to Doma─my lord was eager to see these living legends up close.
Much as I'd like to welcome you in, Blunderville Square is undergoing maintenance at the moment.
To enter Blunderville Square, you must proceed through the quest “Just Crowning Around,” which can be undertaken by speaking with Lewena at Entrance Square.
Such intriguing creatures, these water imps. If I am ever fortunate enough to dream of them, I would invite them to our Hatching–tide festivities without delay.

Perhaps one day, they might even decipher our language and speak with us more candidly... I once welcomed a curious talking rabbit to our celebrations, and I would welcome talking imps with equal enthusiasm!

Do you love MGP? Then you best get yourself over to the Gold Saucer and make the most of the fifty percent bonus rewards on offer during this season's limited-time event! Did I mention it's only for a limited time!?

Do you love MGP? Then you best get yourself over to the Gold Saucer and make the most of the fifty percent bonus rewards on offer during this season's limited-time event! Did I mention it's only for a limited time!?

Do you love MGP? Then you best get yourself over to the Gold Saucer and make the most of the fifty percent bonus rewards on offer during this season's limited-time event! Did I mention it's only for a limited time!?
\\<sigh> I pray that Loashkana is safe... Would that I could send a healer to her side.
Come what may, so long as I have customers, I will continue to fulfill their needs. Now then─can I interest you in a packet of Angel Snacks?
Khloe used to think snakes were awful, squirmy, scaly beasts, but thanks to those fellows from the Far East, I think I've had a change of heart!
Apparently, there's this one serpent─the Great White Tsuchinoko─that's almost impossible to find. Though Khloe bets with all the adventuring you do, you'll come across it sooner or later!
You've already crossed paths with it!? That's incredible!
Now that I'm no longer an Adder, I had no choice but to hand in my uniform. With my new garb, I'm ready to fend off forest-dwelling fiends alongside Keshkwa.
Our donors were pleased to hear that Mistress Tataru's necklace was successfully restored. I am so grateful for their cooperation!
Preparing and distributing both our regular line of equipment and wares from Palaka's Stand is no small task, but I find it deeply fulfilling.
Countess Arabelle was not only a dignified lady, but a noble knight with the resolve and grace to see her passions realized. Tell me, do you know how she developed such fortitude?

Well, I have heard it said that the countess would train at dawn and dusk each day, eschewing the wooden training buckler for her hefty heart-shaped shield─such effort would undoubtedly strengthen both body and mind.
...Pardon me? You believe I shouldn't put stock in such tales? But it sounds perfectly reasonable to me...
Astrid has dedicated herself to making sure Valentione's Day is a smashing success, so it's only right I do the same!
As ever, I'll support her as best I can, and I hope you'll continue to lend us a hand when the need arises!
I am happy to report that Hortefense and I have been having such a splendid time that our little misunderstanding has entirely left our minds.
And, now that I've assuaged any of your lingering concerns, I bid you go enjoy the festivities yourself.
Ah, forgive me. I was just reflecting on Lisette's passionate display earlier.
...I fear my heart has yet to recover.
Look, kupo! All this ardor and affection is making my pom shine brighter than a star!
If the heart is a symbol of Countess Arabelle, does that mean our heart-shaped poms are a sign of her blessing?
Kweh!♪
If yer fixin' to 'ave one of 'em 'eart-shaped chocolates, ye can pick 'em up from the purveyor 'ere.

I'll 'ave ye know their flavor is as rich as their 'istory. Some 'undreds o' years ago, the Culinarians' Guild was honored by House Valentione with the sole privilege o' baking these 'eart-shaped treats, ye see.
An' there ain't no better time than the season o' ardor an' affection to delight in 'em, is there? They're delectable as they come, so make sure ye get 'em while the gettin's good!
A lovely pose for a lovely festival. Tell me, how much better is my rendition than Bert's?
Behold! Bert the Beloved's dazzling embodiment of love puts Rodrigault's to shame, does it not!?
Welcome to Blunderville Square! If you'd like to learn more about our shows, then you've come to the right place.
Greetings! Ready to stumble on into Blunderville Square?
Heading back to Wonder Square, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>madam<Else/>sir</If>?
I meant to take a break from this “show” business, but I happened upon this odd little bird instead...and now I can't stop staring at it! What if it falls over and no one's around to pick it back up?
...What am I thinking about, you ask? Those Beans, of course! It's not every day you come across a band of sentient legumes.
...Oh! Hello, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>. Our lab cats are still in fine and fluffy form, thanks to you. ...Research? O-Oh, yes, it's proceeding apace as well.

Marcette proposed that, in ancient times, levitational magicks were woven into the very essence of various life-forms, thus allowing for the latent ability to be passed down through generations and survive into the present day.

Having witnessed incidents of impromptu flight myself, her theory certainly feels credible. These flight-gifted organisms simply rise from the ground as though, by will alone, they can free themselves from the constraints of natural law... Fascinating, really.

Hyaaagh! I-I mean, good <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If> <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>! Off to face some fearsome foes?
Our latest works transcend the very bounds of excellence, if I do say so myself. With these new and improved arms and armor, even the scariest corners of the realm will be your oyster!
...So if you happen upon heretofore unknown monsters, we would greatly appreciate any information or, er, reproductions you might have to offer!
In stepping away from work more regularly I find myself rewarded with a serendipitous encounter. A pleasure to see you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>.

We installed a prototype of the aforementioned heating apparatus in the refreshment room. Somewhat predictably, the underfed and overworked researchers have, on multiple occasions, disregarded the guidelines for what constitutes “viable foodstuffs.”

And so we are deliberating fail-safes to prevent future combustion and meltdown incidents. I tell you, <split(<String>ObjectParameter(1)</String>, ,1)>, never before have I seen such sticky devastation...
Care for a round of Triple Triad? Something tells me I'll be waiting around to hear the elementals for quite some time.
Why, my victory must be a blessing from the Matron Herself! I hope the elementals will look fondly upon it...wherever they are.
Matron's teats, you're skilled at─oh, dear. I mustn't speak Her name in vain when I am but fulms away from Her altar! I pray the elementals weren't privy to that...
A draw, is it? Perhaps we should take this as a sign─Nophica would prefer we sow the seeds of goodwill over those of rivalry and discontent.
I have heard all manner of curious rumors about you from Snoegeim─that you are blessed by the Twelve, for one. I should like to determine if my colleague speaks true.
Thaliak has gifted me with a keen sense of strategy, and I daresay a round of Triple Triad would allow us to discover if He and His heavenly fellows have done the same for you.

Alas, it appears there will be no divine intervention for you this day. The Scholar's sagacity is noticeably absent from your hand. Perhaps the blessings Snoegeim mentioned were of a more figurative nature?
Consider me impressed. Your every move served as a bold revelation to your reasoning! Now that I have seen your supernatural skills for myself, I am inclined to believe Snoegeim's tales.
Our wits are evenly matched, but my initial query remains unanswered... Another round may tip the ewer of knowledge in your favor, should you desire it.

You, my friend, have the look of a <If(PlayerParameter(4))>woman<Else/>man</If> who has yet to experience Blunderville. I recommend you make for the attraction's gates─our associate there would be pleased to assist you further.
To enter Blunderville Square, you must proceed through the quest “Just Crowning Around,” which can be undertaken by speaking with Lewena at Entrance Square.

A very good <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If> to you, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>madam<Else/>sir</If>. If it's Blunderville you seek, I would be happy to assist you.
I've been waiting a good while now to hear the elementals. When will they favor me with a sign, I wonder...
Whenever I want for inspiration, I like to come here to gaze at the Scholar and the sea. It never fails to clear the mind and give me new perspectives from which to tackle my research into mythology.
Master Grenoldt's making good progress with his breathing exercises, so he should be ready to head to the Exedra shortly. We'll meet you there as soon as we're able!

This establishment caters to lost souls seeking their true path. As a matter of fact, the services of our fortune-teller are in rather high demand of late... I'm afraid we're completely booked for the coming months.

Verifying registration number... Verification complete. Welcome, guest of Queen Sphene. This is Resolution, the operational center of Solution Nine. If you have any queries, please present yourself at the counter inside the facility.
Welcome to the government sector. This facility deals with matters pertaining to employment and welfare. Please let me know if you require assistance.
Here, we manage the distribution and exchange of soul cells. If you give me a moment I can confirm your details and regulator status─ah, it appears you aren't registered in the citizen database...
This is the elevator hall. I'm afraid only authorized individuals are allowed access. Thank you for your understanding.
This is the place to come if you've got any issues with work and whatnot. I'm getting married, so I thought I'd try and wrangle a better-paid position. Has to be worth a shot, right?
I'm glad they approved my housing request, but when I went to move in, there was somebody still living there! You should've seen the official's face when I told them what had happened...
Come to do a bit of shopping? Well, you picked the right place. The commerce sector's probably the best retail hub in all of Everkeep. I'm sure you'll find what you're looking for!
Welcome to Mosaic─a place for folks from all walks of life to mingle and mesh like the patterned stones of a...well, you get the picture. If you like coffee, I recommend our original blend.
Current location: residential radius 9-14, section 01. Scanning visitor log... No entry detected for your registration number.
Current location: residential radius 9-14, section 02. Visitors must be equipped with a regulator or present a valid visitor permit.
I tell you, the commute from here to work is enough to take it out of me... Which is why I take every opportunity I can to unwind and appreciate the greenery!
All the residential radii are laid out like this: with gardens right outside the entrance. I love coming here to relax. Technology's great, but we'll always need trees and plants, you know?
Don't think I've seen you before. You don't live here, do you? Listen, we residents don't take too kindly to folk just wandering in here unannounced...
These residential radii are so different to my village back home. There's no sense of community, for a start. I know some prefer it that way, but I feel more secure when I know who my neighbors are.
I sell all sorts. Just took a delivery of some flavored nutrient drinks─not too bad, if you ask me. Oh, and the candy that makes your belly glow is pretty popular. Interested?
Whenever I lay eyes on a traveler like yourself, I think back to the days I roamed the land as a young lass. Such fond memories...
Can you smell that rich aroma wafting in the air? It comes from this here coffee─a delicious brew made from the coffee beans produced at Ciblu's Coffee Grounds.
Have you had a chance to visit Miplu's Mate Garden? It's a little bit out of the way, but the mate field is well worth seeing.
Welcome, welcome! Urqopacha is terribly cold, isn't it? Come, sit down and have a cup─you'll warm right up!

Say, are you curious about our traditional garments? They're a source of pride for us. We are able to produce this distinctive hue and weave the fabric in this way through a special method passed down through the generations.
The storm may have damaged a number of our caravans... They must be inspected before they can safely be used for travel.
Do you wish to see how mezcal is made? As a distiller myself, it always brings me joy to see others take an interest in our craft!
Alpacas are sensitive creatures. Many of the goods for caring for them come at a great cost, but that is a small price to pay for their happiness.
Welcome to “the house of the Pelupelu,” Wachunpelo! We have many local specialties on offer here, so please have a look around!
Agave Jaws lies north of here, but I must urge caution if you're headed in that direction. There have been countless sightings of monsters in the area of late.
This here is the Family Ranch where we raise alpacas. Their fluffy fleece, wiggly ears, and curious capriciousness are just the best, aren't they?
Have you spoken with Yavli yonder? He loves alpacas dearly, but the feeling does not appear to be mutual─not with this lot, at any rate.
This is where we dry harvested coffee beans. We mix them by hand to ensure each and every bean is thoroughly dried.
Do you see the fruits on the plants here? Those, my friend, are coffee berries. After a lengthy process, they'll become the delicious coffee many have come to know and love.
To the west you will find Miplu's Mate Garden. While I enjoy a cup of mate tea as much anyone else, coffee is quite lovely as well, don't you think?

I inspect coffee beans here before they're shipped out, paying particular attention to the weight of each sack. All of our beans are of premium quality, and we cannot afford even the slightest miscalculation in our measurements.
Have you ever seen someone picking mate leaves? I imagine the opportunities to see such are few and far between.
Hello, friend. It pleases me to see a traveler come visit us here, so far out of the way.
Greetings! I take it you're a traveler? If you are looking for a place to rest this eve, we have beds of varying sizes to accommodate guests of all proportions!
Urqopacha is home to the Pelupelu, and many merchants like myself make the journey to these mountains to trade with them.
They are gracious enough to offer us beds in the inn and a dip in the hot springs at bargain prices. I must admit, being received with such hospitality puts me in high spirits.
Welcome to Panaqpelu Retreat! Pray let down your burdens and enjoy our spacious springs as you take in the breathtaking view!

A merchant hired me as a guard to protect him and his wares on the journey to these mountains, but he bade me rest in the springs while he attends to his negotiations. I do not look forward to leaving this place...

One may immerse their body in the heat of these springs whilst feeling the gentle brush of the wind on their face. Gazing upon this vista in such a state brings complete peace of mind and soothes the spirit...

Ah, hello there. In case you were wondering, I am preparing medicine─it so happens that I am rather gifted with the delicate and precise process of alchemy. Should you ever be in need of succor, pray come and find me.
I must see to preparing a delicious meal for everyone─nothing buoys the spirit like a scrumptious repast.
I am one well versed in matters of the spiritual and inconceivable, yet even I am unable to foresee the outcome of the rite of succession. I can only pray for continued peace in this land.
It is paramount that we keep vigil at all times, as many an unnerving creature roams these lands. If you intend to leave the safety of these walls, you would be wise to act with care.
What do you think of our garden? Magnificent, isn't it?
We live in houses of stone, spacious and sturdy enough for even a group of us to reside in. Yet I fear the doors may be rather too heavy to open for anyone besides us...
Before you lies Karryorzar the Gracious. See to it that you comport yourself with dignity.
This is the Indelible Passage. It is our duty to safeguard the murals left behind by our ancestors, and we take many measures to ensure the beasts of the wild cannot draw near them.
We were just discussing the claimants in the rite of succession. Though they may be smaller in stature than we, each of them are impressive in their own right.
Anything and everything that passes between the northern and southern lands of Tural must do so across this bridge. You'd be surprised how much cargo we can see in a day.
This saloon is more than just a place to be deep in your cups. With so many merchants passing through town, there's valuable information to be had here.
Fancy a drink before you head out into the wilds?
We don't pick just any ol' tuna. It has to be ripe, it has to be fresh! Nothing goes in these crates unless it's absolutely perfect.
They may not look it, but rroneek are some of the gentlest creatures you'll ever see. Can't imagine where we'd be without them.
Hrruff...
We'll be in for a treat when these cacti are ready for picking.
What's your business? Come to pay someone's bail? Or, perhaps, you're here to file a complaint?
Have you tried the nopales served here at the saloon? Some of the most filling and refreshing fare you can find here in Hhusatahwi.
Ah, I see you have a travel pass. Right this way, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>miss<Else/>sir</If>.
If you've a favorite dancer, I suggest you stop by the dance hall often. We've so many coming and going, I can scarcely keep track of who's performing next.
You hear that...? Blissful silence. A commodity that was woefully in short supply before the Dustwatch was founded.
Shouldn't be long now before my popotoes are done. Just in time for my boy to come home from working at the Springs.
You know, these rock formations have protected the people of Luwateninyawawsa from heavy rain and roaming beasts for generations. They might even be why we decided to live here in the first place.
My family has used these kilns for generations. I can scarcely imagine life without them.
A merchant come from Tuliyollal recently sold me supplies for my garden, and I must say─it's amazing what a difference quality fertilizer can make.
We're running low on dried meats, so I may need to go hunting soon. Or maybe I should tend to the crops first...
I know the fish will be done soon, but I'm so godsdamned hungry!
\\<sigh> I just need to wait a little while longer...
This here's the office for the ceruleum refinery. An important meeting is taking place right now, so I can't let you in.
Things are quiet now, but if there should be trouble, we'll be glad to have this equipment in good condition.

To tell the truth, I miss life back in Luwateninyawawsa. Still, I'm earning good money in the ceruleum business, maybe even enough to support my pa in his retirement. Not that he'd accept any “charity” from me, though!
I swear I just washed these sheets, then the wind had to go and kick up more dirt. \\<sigh> Time for another rinse.
The worst thing about moving those barrels over there is how the ceruleum leaks through the cracks. It's dirty business in every sense of the word.
There's no shortage of work here, but sadly there's not much else to do. If you're looking to have a good time, best make for Hhusatahwi.
New around here? Why not join me for a drink?
If you're here for the fishing, make sure you don't touch any of your catches with your bare hands, or you'll be in for a shock!
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... Many, many warmhearted welcomings to Many Fires. Swipostik wishes you a comfyfeeling stay!
I knew the storm was going to be bad, but I never imagined it would be quite so bad as to bring down the Flight of We Wingless. Now I'm completely stuck!
I deal with Moblins all the time, so I figured I'd ask around and find out what kind of goods they're interested in. Market research, if you will.
Doesn't look like the caravan to Earthenshire will be leaving any time soon. Perhaps the Moblins might slip me a few gil to keep the nasties from the gates while I wait.

Like most folk, I'm stuck here until the roads open up again. But unlike most folk, I've got a wagonload of fresh fruit with me. Hungry travelers with nowhere to go? Could be some good money to be made.
Pfffkohhh... Since the bigsteps went splintersmash in the storm, lots of lowlanders are journeyblocked. Chekochuk will make them tastygrub to take rattyfeels away!
It may take many moons to rebuild the great stairs, but just like those who once climbed it, we shall take the repairs one step at a time, until we finally achieve our goal.
It brings a tear to my eye to see our ancestors' creation reduced to little more than a pile of scattered sticks. On our honor as wingless ones, we will see it rebuilt.
The storm swept through like a terrible beast, destroying all in its path. With the trade routes in disarray, we must seek out other means to bring in the lumber to repair the stairs.
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... So many pots went smashshards... Perhaps if we powdersmashed the smashshards and mixed the potpowder with craftclay, we could make freshpots from the smashpots?
It is a very important mobduty to find the perfect craftstuff for our potsworn.
Moblin helphands are always wideeyes and bigears for new sources of goodgrade craftstuff!
Every day we Moblins are fullhanded, sweatbrowed, and footrushed helping our potsworn.
But when we see the tricksycrafted treasures that they craftmake for us, it is all worthwhile!
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... What will the crowning of the new Dawnservant mean for Earthenshire, Tempatriq wonders? She hearthopes there will still be a place for potsworn and helphands in the new Tural.
Pfff... Pfffkohhh... It is hearthappying to hear that Many Fires outlived the storm, but sadeyes that the bigstairs did not.
Until they are backbuilt, trading with the Hanuhanu will be a trickytask.
Pfff... So much craftystuff went clattercrash and squishsquelch in the bigwind and the badrain. Must order more before the potsworn outrun their supplies.

The fish we catch in these waters are delicious stuffed with herbs and roasted over an open flame, or slow-stewed with chilies to make a warming soup, or else...no, I must say no more, or I shall collapse from hunger!
The Hanu's reed magicks are endlessly fascinating. Beware delving too deeply into the traditions that bind them to the land, lest they cast their spell on you, too.
Watch your head, friend. The storm went at our thatching like a coeurl in an alpaca stable. Until we get it relaid, the slightest breeze is wont to summon a rain of reeds.
It is always wise to prepare for a rainy day─as the most recent one made crystal clear. We used most of our boards in repairing the damage. Now I must cut and plane more to prepare for the next.

If only we wingless could fly, we would not need our Flight to reach the communities upriver. As we are, we rely on trading routes of our own making─and when they are cut off, so too is the lifeblood of trade.
We pray for the wind's blessing, then she goes and carries off half our reed stores! Would that it would guide them back to us as well, but no─that's a job for her oh-so-faithful servants!
Ohokaliy, friend. I bid you welcome to Ok'hanu─and bid you watch your footing, too. Much of the ground is still muddy since the storm.
Food is the fuel that keeps the fire inside us burning bright─and I the tender to that eternal flame, who keeps it fed with beaksome meals!
The storm came through like a band of brigands, seeking to browbeat us into submission.
Not only did it make a show of its strength by tossing heavy crates and furniture as if they were a fledgling's playthings, it proved its savagery by trying to pluck out our feathers, too!
Like the ever-shifting clouds, it's still up in the air who will be chosen as the next Dawnservant. Whoever is chosen, I pray that peace will still reign here after they are crowned.
It feels like the end of an era for Gulool Ja Ja to be stepping down from the throne. No─it is the end of an era.
But his retirement is both long awaited and well deserved. Perhaps he will spend some of it here in Ok'hanu? If he did, he would be very welcome.

Ohokaliy! We are graced with a good wind this <If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),12))><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),4))>evening<Else/>morning</If><Else/><If(LessThan(PlayerParameter(11),17))>day<Else/>evening</If></If>! Truly, there is magic in the air!
Do you like heights, stranger? I do─if not for the magnificent views, then for the bracing breeze that tickles one's feathers. Pray stay awhile and enjoy them with me.
Just finished my latest painting, and not a bad job I made of it, either. The question now is, do I start up on the next piece straightaway, while my eye's in, or have a celebratory knees-up?
I appreciate you showing an interest, but I can't let you inside. It's far too dangerous.
The lack of hunters really has us in a bind. We never had this much difficulty in seeking their protection before.
It just goes to show how vital spare souls are. Now that there are fewer available for revival, the number of hunters prepared to venture the plains is plummeting.
I can tell you've a good eye, and I'm not talking about your ocular capabilities. What I mean is that you seem to be well suited to finding lost valuables, useful resources, and the like.
If you've a mind to become a reforger, I'm certain you'd go far. As a possessor of a good eye myself, I'd bet on it!
The things we find are used in one of two ways: for ourselves, or passed on to others.
We meet all sorts of...interesting individuals, and over time, we gradually build a large network of contacts.
Living off of the land is hard enough, even without all the electricity to contend with. More than a few of us have come down with ailments caused by overexposure to it.
This is the apparatus used to deliver vegetables. As we can't leave them outside for too long, we use an automated system to send them through underground conduits.
Oh, are you on a break, too? We were just talking about the Halo.
For years, no one was officially in charge of the place. But recently, someone raised in the outskirts was given the position. Personally, I'm all for it.
Sorry, I'm a little busy. I must organize these resources before they can be traded in Everkeep.
Hmm... Whatever should I cook? I suppose I'd better make the most of the fresh produce I have at my fingertips.
If you see any oglops out there, be sure to let me know! You wouldn't believe the trouble they can cause.
Even if it's for research purposes, I simply cannot stand being out here. With all the lightning and whatnot, only a fool would choose to live in a place like this.
Ah, are you newly come to Living Memory?
Please, take your time looking around. You will find a place that suits you in due course.
There's nothing more relaxing than the gentle rocking of a gondola. Please, have a seat. I plan to remain here a while yet.

A most wondrous thing has happened─my mother was recently reunited with a good friend of hers. I imagine they're doing their best to make up for lost time, speaking of all that has happened since last they met.
Indeed, I expect it will be some time until she returns, so I was thinking of procuring a few snacks to pass the time. Perhaps some popcorn to start...
I do so love the view of the city from here. The picturesque scene of passersby against the skyline is absolutely perfect.
But the Endless have greatly diminished, the buildings in the distance have grown dark... What will come next, I wonder?
Welcome to the Bergmähr-Ring. Please enjoy your stay.
They can't decide if they'd rather ride the Bergmähr-Ring or the esperance wheels. Me? I just wish they would make up their minds so we can go already!
We were enjoying ourselves in the hot springs, but then my son here got a little lightheaded. We'll be heading back after a little break, and perhaps a little ice cream.
I look away for only a moment and she goes off and buys another ice cream cone. What if I wanted one, too?

I am authorized to attend lost patrons if you require assistance. I may also request the presence of others if so desired. Please be advised, however, a request cannot be made of those yet to become Endless.
Welcome to Matchlock Menagerie. I'm afraid there are no longer any animals left, but you're free to take your ease here if you so desire.
Care for refreshments, <If(PlayerParameter(4))>miss<Else/>sir</If>? All purchases come with a free plush doll, free of charge, while supplies last.
I'll not deny my work as a courier was fulfilling, but look around. We have everything we could ever want here.
After purchasing refreshments, you're free to sit at one of our tables, if you like. Or you can simply take it with you if you prefer.
The greenery here is breathtaking, would you not agree? Lush, fragrant, and─for a mercy─free of insects.
I find beetles in particular to be repulsive. I've seen none as of yet, but I fear it's only a matter of time before they rear their despicable heads.
Yes, that should do nicely.
Oh, this? I'm using electrope technology to prepare this fertilizer. We can easily adjust the humidity and airflow, which─if you know anything about this sort of thing─is rather useful.
This here dirigible flies between Yak T'el and Tuliyollal. Thanks to the technology Koana brought back from beyond the salt, we've established a route that goes over the dense forests of this region.
It's only been three years since the dirigibles were built, but I can't imagine life without them. If you're keen to soar through the skies, just ask the landing attendant!
